<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="352" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,332,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Head covered with ca. 
<number box="[583,611,332,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="26.0">26</number>
scattered interfrontal setulae, eyes with three transverse light stripes (well noted when the specimen is preserved in alcohol). Scutum and scutellum brownish covered with small dark brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[226,295,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[280,295,404,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b), pleura yellowish with two large dark brown longitudinal stripes, abdomen yellowish with brown stripes in each tergite medially widely interrupted and laterally connected (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1088,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[1074,1088,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a–b). Wings hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1410,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[1394,1410,440,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Male terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[395,488,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1288,1310]" captionTargetBox="[417,1169,193,1266]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[417,1169,193,1267]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male terminalia of the holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a – c: aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme. a: dorsal view; b: ventral view; c: lateral view; d: epandrium, cerci and surstyli, caudal view (scale bar: 0.05 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399948/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Figure 
<number box="[475,488,476,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
a–d.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="354" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Description</emphasis>
. ♂. Head (
<figureCitation box="[475,547,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[532,547,512,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a; 
<number box="[578,592,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
d–e). Front brownish, covered with ca. 
<number box="[1062,1090,511,536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="26.0">26</number>
scattered interfrontal setulae, frontal length 
<quantity box="[309,401,548,573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57mm</quantity>
(
<number box="[416,535,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.5700000000000001" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.56">0.56–0.58</number>
); frontal index = 
<number box="[727,776,548,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.14">1.14</number>
(
<number box="[791,909,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.1400000000000001" valueMax="1.16" valueMin="1.12">1.12–1.16</number>
); top-to-bottom width ratio = 
<number box="[1242,1291,548,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.09">1.09</number>
(
<number box="[1306,1424,548,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.09" valueMax="1.12" valueMin="1.06">1.06–1.12</number>
); ocellar triangle to front length ratio = 
<number box="[571,620,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.42">0.42</number>
(
<number box="[634,752,583,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.42000000000000004" valueMax="0.46" valueMin="0.38">0.38–0.46</number>
); or 
<number box="[796,805,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.0">1</number>
/or 
<number box="[841,853,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="3.0">3</number>
ratio = 
<number box="[939,988,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.08">1.08</number>
(
<number box="[1003,1121,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.08" valueMax="1.09" valueMin="1.07">1.07–1.09</number>
); or 
<number box="[1165,1179,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
/or 
<number box="[1213,1222,584,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.0">1</number>
ratio = 
<number box="[1308,1357,583,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.61">0.61</number>
(
<number pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.61" valueMax="0.64" valueMin="0.58">0.58– 0.64</number>
); vibrissal index = 
<number box="[432,481,620,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.43">0.43</number>
(
<number box="[500,618,620,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="0.43" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.36">0.36–0.50</number>
). Carina prominent. Cheek index = 
<number box="[1040,1089,620,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="8.1">8.10</number>
(
<number box="[1107,1212,620,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="8.1" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="6.7">6.7–9.50</number>
). Eye index = 
<number box="[1387,1436,620,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.31">1.31</number>
(
<number box="[159,277,655,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.31" valueMax="1.35" valueMin="1.27">1.27–1.35</number>
). Antenna with the tip of flagellomeres darker brown, arista with short branches, 
<number box="[1180,1208,656,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="12.0">12</number>
dorsal branches and 
<number box="[151,179,692,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="10.0">10</number>
ventral branches plus terminal fork. Palpus yellowish with ca. 
<number box="[882,910,692,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="15.0">15</number>
setae on lower part. Eyes with three transverse light stripes (
<figureCitation box="[298,364,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[350,364,727,752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d) (well noted when the specimen is preserved in alcohol).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[294,360,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1005,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,1005,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Holotype of R. trivisualis sp. nov. a: general habitus, lateral view; b: general habitus, dorsal view; c: wing; d: eyes with three light stripes (indicated by the arrows, in alcohol); e: head, frontal view (scale bar 1.0 mm in a, b, c and d; 0.5 mm in e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/399947/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Fig. 
<number box="[346,360,764,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a–b). Thorax length 
<quantity box="[588,680,764,789]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.60mm</quantity>
(
<number box="[695,813,764,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="1.6" valueMax="1.68" valueMin="1.52">1.52–1.68</number>
). Scutum and scutellum brownish; scutum covered with many small dark brown spots. 
<number box="[503,531,800,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="10.0">10</number>
rows of acrostichal setulae. 
<number box="[858,872,800,824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of prescutellar acrostichal setae, the central pair strongest, about 
<number box="[405,434,836,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="56.0">56</number>
% (
<number box="[478,551,836,861]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="56.0" valueMax="64.0" valueMin="48.0">48–64</number>
) of posterior dorsocentral setae. Postpronotum with one setae. Transverse distance between dorsocentral setae 
<number box="[557,606,872,896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="3.32">3.32</number>
x (
<number box="[634,749,871,896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" value="3.325" valueMax="3.85" valueMin="2.8">2.80–3.85</number>
) longitudinal distance. Basal scutellar setae divergent. Sterno index = 
